called Chef... was from New Orleans. </i>

234
00:21:14,495 --> 00:21:17,373
<i>He was wrapped too tight
for Vietnam. </i>

235
00:21:17,498 --> 00:21:20,210
<i>Probably wrapped too tight
for New Orleans. </i>

236
00:21:20,336 --> 00:21:22,254
<i>Lance, on the forward fifties... </i>

237
00:21:22,379 --> 00:21:25,132
<i>was a famous surfer
from the beaches south of L.A. </i>

238
00:21:25,215 --> 00:21:29,054
<i>To look at him, you wouldn't believe
he'd ever fired a weapon in his life. </i>

239
00:21:30,930 --> 00:21:35,144
<i>Clean... Mr. Clean... was
from some South Bronx shit-hole... </i>

240
00:21:35,227 --> 00:21:37,397
<i>and I think the light
and the space of Vietnam... </i>

241
00:21:37,522 --> 00:21:41,109
<i>really put the zap on his head. </i>

242
00:21:42,527 --> 00:21:45,156
<i>Then there was Phillips,
the chief. </i>

243
00:21:45,239 --> 00:21:49,161
<i>It might have been my mission, but
it sure as shit was the chief’s boat. </i>

244
00:21:49,286 --> 00:21:51,205
There's about two points
where we can draw enough water...

245
00:21:51,330 --> 00:21:53,707
to get into the Nung River.

246
00:21:53,832 --> 00:21:57,962
They're both hot.
Belong to Charlie.

247
00:21:58,088 --> 00:22:00,465
Don't worry about it.

248
00:22:00,591 --> 00:22:03,678
Don't smoke.

249
00:22:03,803 --> 00:22:06,932
You know, I've pulled
a few special ops in here.

250
00:22:07,057 --> 00:22:09,643
About six months ago...

251
00:22:09,768 --> 00:22:14,065
I took a man who was going up
past the bridge at Do Lung.

252
00:22:14,190 --> 00:22:16,859
He was regular army too.

253
00:22:18,904 --> 00:22:22,324
Heard he shot himself
in the head.

254
00:22:30,251 --> 00:22:34,130
<i>At first I thought
they handed me the wrong dossier. </i>

255
00:22:34,255 --> 00:22:36,800
<i>I couldn't believe
they wanted this man dead. </i>

256
00:22:38,427 --> 00:22:41,305
<i>Third-generation West Point,
top of his class. </i>

257
00:22:41,431 --> 00:22:45,643
<i>Korea, Airborne,
about a thousand decorations. </i>

258
00:22:45,768 --> 00:22:47,771
<i>Et cetera, et cetera. </i>

259
00:22:50,357 --> 00:22:55,280
<i>I'd heard his voice on the tape,
and it really put the hook in me... </i>

260
00:22:55,405 --> 00:22:59,994
<i>but I couldn't connect up
that voice with this man. </i>

261
00:23:06,126 --> 00:23:09,963
<i>Like they said,
he had an impressive career. </i>

262
00:23:10,088 --> 00:23:14,969
<i>Maybe too impressive.
I mean, perfect. </i>

263
00:23:15,094 --> 00:23:19,308
<i>He was being groomed for one of
the top slots in the corporation... </i>

264
00:23:19,433 --> 00:23:22,729
<i>general, chief of staff,
anything. </i>

265
00:23:24,439 --> 00:23:28,444
<i>In 1964, he returned from a tour
with Advisory Command in Vietnam... </i>

266
00:23:28,569 --> 00:23:30,905
<i>and things started to slip. </i>

267
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:33,115
<i>His report to
the Joint Chiefs of Staff... </i>

268
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,661
<i>and Lyndon Johnson was restricted. </i>

269
00:23:37,371 --> 00:23:41,125
<i>Seems they didn't dig
what he had to tell them. </i>

270
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:44,170
<i>During the next few months, he
made three requests for transfer... </i>

271
00:23:44,295 --> 00:23:49,343
<i>to Airborne training, Fort Benning,
Georgia, and was finally accepted. </i>

272
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:54,474
<i>Airborne? </i>

273
00:23:56,434 --> 00:23:59,105
<i>He was 38 years old. </i>

274
00:24:00,189 --> 00:24:02,483
<i>Why the fuck would he do that? </i>

275
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:09,075
<i>1966, joins Special Forces... </i>

276
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,160
<i>returns to Vietnam. </i>

277
00:24:11,452 --> 00:24:13,454
Hey, what's that?

278
00:24:13,579 --> 00:24:16,083
- Arc light.
- What's up?

279
00:24:16,208 --> 00:24:18,752
- B-52 strike.
- Yeah?

280
00:24:18,877 --> 00:24:20,755
- What's that?
- Arc light.

281
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:23,800
I hate that. Every time I hear that,
something terrible happens.

282
00:24:23,925 --> 00:24:25,802
Charlie don't never
see 'em or hear 'em, man.

283
00:24:25,927 --> 00:24:27,179
There they are.

284
00:24:27,263 --> 00:24:29,557
Concussion will suck the air
out of your damn lungs.

285
00:24:29,682 --> 00:24:31,684
Something terrible
is gonna happen.

286
00:24:31,809 --> 00:24:35,439
Smoke! Secondary burning.

287
00:24:35,564 --> 00:24:38,067
Hueys over there. Lots of Hueys.

288
00:24:38,192 --> 00:24:41,070
Let's have a look, Chief.

289
00:24:41,195 --> 00:24:44,783
<i>It was the Air-Cav.
First of the Ninth... </i>

290
00:24:44,908 --> 00:24:45,701
That's them.

291
00:24:45,826 --> 00:24:48,704
<i>our escorts to the mouth
of the Nung River. </i>

292
00:24:48,829 --> 00:24:52,667
<i>But they were supposed to be waiting
for us another 30 kilometres ahead. </i>

293
00:24:52,792 --> 00:24:57,965
<i>Well, Air Mobile.
Those boys just couldn't stay put. </i>

294
00:25:09,645 --> 00:25:12,607
Hey, kid, come on.
Get down. Come on.

295
00:25:23,661 --> 00:25:26,540
<i>First of the Ninth was
an old cavalry division... </i>

296
00:25:26,665 --> 00:25:28,542
<i>that had cashed in its horses
for choppers... </i>

297
00:25:28,667 --> 00:25:32,547
<i>and gone tear-assing around
'Nam looking for the shit. </i>

298
00:25:32,672 --> 00:25:37,220
<i>They'd given Charlie
a few surprises in their time here. </i>

299
00:25:37,345 --> 00:25:42,184
<i>What they were mopping up now hadn't
even happened yet an hour ago. </i>

300
00:25:42,309 --> 00:25:44,561
Just keeping running by.
We're for television.

301
00:25:44,687 --> 00:25:46,980
Don't look at the camera.
Just keep... Go on. Keep going.

302
00:25:47,106 --> 00:25:48,983
This is for television.
Don't look at the camera.

303
00:25:49,109 --> 00:25:52,362
Just go by like you're fighting,
like you're fighting.

304
00:25:52,487 --> 00:25:56,033
Don't look at the camera.
It's for television. Just go through.

305
00:25:56,158 --> 00:25:58,119
Just go by. Keep on going.

306
00:25:58,244 --> 00:26:00,372
Keep going. Don't look at the camera.
Go on. Keep going.

307
00:26:00,497 --> 00:26:02,332
All right, come on. Go.

308
00:26:07,422 --> 00:26:09,382
Right here. Yes.
Over here. Over here.

309
00:26:23,357 --> 00:26:25,735
Where can I find the CO?

310
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:30,032
That's the colonel comin' down!

311
00:26:38,291 --> 00:26:40,961
The CO's on that chopper.

312
00:27:03,236 --> 00:27:06,741
Lieutenant, bomb that tree line
back about 100 yards!

313
00:27:06,866 --> 00:27:09,995
- Give me some room to breathe!
- Yes, sir!

314
00:27:14,750 --> 00:27:15,960
Body cards!

315
00:27:16,086 --> 00:27:18,129
- Sir?
- Bring my body cards!

316
00:27:18,254 --> 00:27:20,131
Yes, sir!

317
00:27:22,718 --> 00:27:25,971
I'm the Fourth Tank commander.
I got five tanks broken down.

318
00:27:26,097 --> 00:27:29,226
We're all right with the tanks.
It's all right, Captain.

319
00:27:29,351 --> 00:27:30,602
Captain Willard!

320
00:27:30,727 --> 00:27:34,107
I carry priority papers from
Com-Sec Intelligence, II Corps.

321
00:27:34,232 --> 00:27:36,150
I understand Nha Trang
has briefed you...

322
00:27:36,275 --> 00:27:38,152
on the requirements of my mission.

323
00:27:38,277 --> 00:27:40,823
What mission?
I haven't heard from Nha Trang.

324
00:27:40,948 --> 00:27:43,867
Sir, your unit is supposed
to escort us into the Nung!

325
00:27:43,992 --> 00:27:46,162
- We'll see what we can do.
- Colonel!

326
00:27:46,287 --> 00:27:51,043
But just stay out of my way
until this is done, Captain.

327
00:27:53,462 --> 00:27:56,299
All right, let's see what we have.
Let's see what we have.

328
00:27:56,425 --> 00:28:01,471
A two of spades, three of spades,
four of diamonds...

329
00:28:01,596 --> 00:28:04,183
six of clubs, eight of spades.

330
00:28:04,308 --> 00:28:07,353
There isn't one worth a jack
in the whole bunch.

331
00:28:07,478 --> 00:28:10,357
Four of diamonds.

332
00:28:10,482 --> 00:28:14,195
- Hey, Captain, what's that?
- Death cards!

333
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:17,615
- What?
- Death cards!

334
00:28:17,741 --> 00:28:20,077
- Death?
- Lets Charlie know who did this.

335
00:28:23,664 --> 00:28:26,460
<i>- Cheer up, son.
- We will not hurt or harm you. </i>

336
00:28:26,585 --> 00:28:30,297
- Fire in the hole!
- Fire in the hole!

337
00:28:30,589 --> 00:28:34,052
<i>This is an area
that is controlled... </i>

338
00:28:34,177 --> 00:28:36,554
<i>by the Vietcong
and North Vietnamese. </i>

339
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,599
Jim.

340
00:28:42,687 --> 00:28:45,899
<i>We are here to help you. </i>

341
00:28:47,025 --> 00:28:50,988
<i>- We extend a welcome hand...
- Come on.</i>

342
00:28:51,113 --> 00:28:53,157
<i>-to those who would like to return...
- Everybody in?</i>

343
00:28:53,282 --> 00:28:57,579
<i>to the arms of
the South Vietnamese government. </i>

344
00:28:57,704 --> 00:29:01,125
Get in. Hurry up.

345
00:29:02,210 --> 00:29:03,920
Move it out.

346
00:29:04,045 --> 00:29:06,548
<i>This is an area
that is controlled... </i>

347
00:29:06,673 --> 00:29:09,259
<i>by the Vietcong
and North Vietnamese. </i>

348
00:29:09,385 --> 00:29:14,516
Hey! What's this?
What is this?

349
00:29:14,641 --> 00:29:17,310
This man's hurt
pretty bad, sir.

350
00:29:17,435 --> 00:29:20,856
About the only thing that's holding
his guts in, sir, is that pot lid.

351
00:29:20,981 --> 00:29:23,360
Yeah? What do you have to say?

352
00:29:23,485 --> 00:29:29,283
This soldier is dirty VC. He wants
water. He can drink paddy water.

353
00:29:29,409 --> 00:29:32,787
Get outta here!
Give me that canteen.

354
00:29:32,912 --> 00:29:36,041
- He's VC!
- Any man that's brave enough to...

355
00:29:36,166 --> 00:29:38,752
Get outta here!
I'll kick your fuckin' ass!

356
00:29:38,877 --> 00:29:40,964
He killed a lot of our people!

357
00:29:41,089 --> 00:29:43,216
Any man brave enough
to fight with his guts...

358
00:29:43,299 --> 00:29:45,301
strapped on him
can drink from my canteen.

359
00:29:45,427 --> 00:29:49,473
Hey, Colonel, I think one of those
sailors is Lance Johnson, the surfer.

360
00:29:49,598 --> 00:29:53,395
- Where? Here? You sure?
- Down there.

361
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,480
Yeah? Here.

362
00:29:55,605 --> 00:29:58,526
Repeat. We have a body count.
We have...

363
00:30:01,195 --> 00:30:03,239
What's your name, sailor?

364
00:30:03,364 --> 00:30:06,201
- Gunner's Mate Third Class Johnson.
- Gunner's Mate Third Class...

365
00:30:06,285 --> 00:30:10,373
- Lance Johnson, the surfer?
- Yes, sir.

366
00:30:10,498 --> 00:30:14,627
It's an honour to meet you. I've
admired your nose riding for years.

367
00:30:14,753 --> 00:30:17,590
I like your cutback too. I think
you have the best cutback there is.

368
00:30:17,715 --> 00:30:20,342
- Thank you, sir.
- You can cut out the "sir" crap.

369
00:30:20,468 --> 00:30:22,471
I'm Bill Kilgore.
I'm a goofy foot.

370
00:30:22,596 --> 00:30:24,473
- This guy with ya?
- Yeah.

371
00:30:24,598 --> 00:30:26,391
I want you to meet some guys.

372
00:30:26,516 --> 00:30:28,394
- This is Mike from San Diego.
- Far out.

373
00:30:28,519 --> 00:30:31,355
- Johnny from Malibu. Solid surfers.
- John, hi. Far out.

374
00:30:31,481 --> 00:30:33,609
None of us are anywhere
near your class though.

375
00:30:33,734 --> 00:30:35,152
No way.

376
00:30:35,277 --> 00:30:39,157
We do a lot of surfing around here.
I like to finish operations early.

377
00:30:39,282 --> 00:30:41,618
Fly down to Vung Tau
for the evening glass.

378
00:30:41,743 --> 00:30:44,162
Been riding since you got here?

379
00:30:44,287 --> 00:30:46,874
No way. I haven't surfed
since I been here.

380
00:30:46,999 --> 00:30:49,376
Through Christ, our Lord...

381
00:30:49,502 --> 00:30:51,546
from Whom
all good things come...

382
00:30:51,671 --> 00:30:54,257
through Him in the unity
of the Holy Spirit.

383
00:30:54,341 --> 00:30:57,220
All glory and honour
is Yours, Almighty Father.

384
00:30:57,345 --> 00:30:59,764
Let us bring
our iniquities to the Father...

385
00:30:59,889 --> 00:31:01,808
in the words our Saviour gave us.

386
00:31:01,933 --> 00:31:06,855
Our Father, Who art in heaven,
hallowed be Thy name.

387
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:11,611
Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done
on earth as it is in heaven.

388
00:31:11,736 --> 00:31:14,532
Give us this day
our daily bread...

389
00:31:14,657 --> 00:31:16,534
and forgive us our trespasses...

390
00:31:16,659 --> 00:31:18,744
<i>as we forgive those
who trespass against us. </i>

391
00:31:18,869 --> 00:31:22,499
<i>Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil. </i>

392
00:31:31,552 --> 00:31:35,305
<i>Kilgore had had a pretty
good day for himself. </i>

393
00:31:35,431 --> 00:31:37,559
<i>They choppered in
the T-bones and the beer... </i>

394
00:31:37,684 --> 00:31:40,937
<i>and turned the LZ
into a beach party. </i>

395
00:31:41,062 --> 00:31:44,024
<i>The more they tried
to make it just like home... </i>

396
00:31:44,150 --> 00:31:46,777
<i>the more they made
everybody miss it. </i>

397
00:31:46,902 --> 00:31:50,073
Make my meat rare...
rare but not cold.

398
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:59,292
<i>Well, he wasn't
a bad officer, I guess. </i>

399
00:31:59,417 --> 00:32:02,921
<i>He loved his boys,
and you felt safe with him. </i>

400
00:32:03,046 --> 00:32:06,300
<i>He was one of those guys that
had that weird light around him. </i>

401
00:32:06,426 --> 00:32:10,221
<i>You just knew he wasn't gonna
get so much as a scratch here. </i>

402
00:32:10,305 --> 00:32:14,185
What happened to your mission?
Nha Trang forget all about you?

403
00:32:22,235 --> 00:32:25,281
Airborne.

404
00:32:25,406 --> 00:32:28,868
Sir, two places we can
get into the river.

405
00:32:28,993 --> 00:32:31,997
- Yeah.
- Here and here.

406
00:32:32,122 --> 00:32:36,961
It's a pretty wide delta, but these
are the only two spots I'm sure of.

407
00:32:37,087 --> 00:32:40,090
That village you're pointing at
is kind of hairy.

408
00:32:40,215 --> 00:32:42,510
- What do you mean "hairy," sir?
- It's hairy.

409
00:32:42,635 --> 00:32:44,512
Got some pretty heavy ordnance.

410
00:32:44,637 --> 00:32:47,014
I lost a few recon ships
in there now and again.

411
00:32:47,139 --> 00:32:50,352
What's the name of
that goddam village? Vin Drin...

412
00:32:50,477 --> 00:32:52,813
- Dop.
- Dop or Lop?

413
00:32:52,938 --> 00:32:56,526
Damn gook names
all sound the same.

414
00:32:56,651 --> 00:32:59,655
Mike, you know anything about
this point at Vin Drin Dop?

415
00:32:59,780 --> 00:33:01,657
That's a fantastic peak.

416
00:33:01,782 --> 00:33:04,201
- Peak?
- About six foot.

417
00:33:04,326 --> 00:33:07,997
It's an outstanding peak. It's got
both the long right and left slide...

418
00:33:08,123 --> 00:33:10,291
with a bowl section
that's unbelievable.

419
00:33:10,417 --> 00:33:12,795
It's just tube city.

420
00:33:15,589 --> 00:33:18,051
Why didn't you tell me
that before? A good peak.

421
00:33:18,176 --> 00:33:20,846
There aren't any good peaks
in this whole shitty country.

422
00:33:20,971 --> 00:33:22,849
It's all goddam beach break.

423
00:33:22,974 --> 00:33:25,893
It's really hairy in there.
That's where we lost McDonald.

424
00:33:26,018 --> 00:33:30,232
They shot the hell out of us there.
That's Charlie's point.

425
00:33:30,357 --> 00:33:32,734
Sir, we can go in there
tomorrow at dawn.

426
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:34,904
There's always a good
offshore breeze in the morning.

427
00:33:35,029 --> 00:33:36,906
We may not be able
to get the boat in.

428
00:33:37,031 --> 00:33:41,036
The draught at the mouth of
that river may be too shallow.

429
00:33:41,162 --> 00:33:44,081
We'll pick your boat up and put it
down like a baby where you want it.

430
00:33:44,206 --> 00:33:46,710
This is the First of the Ninth,
Air-Cav, son.

431
00:33:46,835 --> 00:33:51,131
Air mobile! I can take that point
and hold it as long as I like.

432
00:33:51,257 --> 00:33:54,302
You can get anyplace up that river
that suits you, young Captain.

433
00:33:54,385 --> 00:33:56,804
Hell, a six-foot peak.

434
00:33:58,056 --> 00:33:59,933
Take a gunship
back to the division.

435
00:34:00,058 --> 00:34:02,102
Lance, go with Mike and let him
pick out a board for you.

436
00:34:02,227 --> 00:34:04,397
Bring me my Yater Spoon,
the eight-six.

437
00:34:04,522 --> 00:34:06,399
- I don't know, sir...
- What is it, soldier?

438
00:34:06,524 --> 00:34:09,570
It's hairy in there.
It's Charlie's point.

439
00:34:09,695 --> 00:34:11,781
Charlie don't surf!

440
00:34:34,933 --> 00:34:38,896
Hey, Jesus, Clean, you ain't
gonna believe this. Look.

441
00:34:40,022 --> 00:34:42,900
Hey, man!
They're pickin' up the boat!

442
00:34:46,113 --> 00:34:50,034
- How are you feeling, Jimmy?
- Like a mean motherfucker, sir!

443
00:34:51,661 --> 00:34:53,621
All right, son, let 'er rip.

444
00:34:53,746 --> 00:34:56,500
Let's go!

445
00:36:18,930 --> 00:36:22,726
I never have got used to a light
board. I can't get used to one.

446
00:36:22,851 --> 00:36:25,729
- I'm used to a heavy board.
- I know, it's a real drag.

447
00:36:25,854 --> 00:36:28,440
- You prefer a heavy or light board?
- Heavier.

448
00:36:28,566 --> 00:36:30,443
- Really?
- Yeah!

449
00:36:30,568 --> 00:36:33,238
I thought all the young guys
like lighter boards.

450
00:36:33,363 --> 00:36:36,450
<i>- You can't ride the nose on those.
- Big Duke Six. </i>

451
00:36:36,575 --> 00:36:38,202
This is Eagle Thrust Seven.
We've got it spotted.

452
00:36:38,327 --> 00:36:39,870
<i>Duke Six to Eagle Thrust. </i>

453
00:36:39,995 --> 00:36:43,416
Put on heading two-seven-zero.
Assume attack formation.

454
00:36:43,542 --> 00:36:45,877
<i>That's a roger, Big Duke.
We're going in. </i>

455
00:36:46,002 --> 00:36:50,049
Hey, Lance, we'll come in
low out of the rising sun.

